    • Method Detail

      • check

        public boolean check(ValidationContext context,
                     T object)
        Description copied from interface: AnyConstraint
        Checks if the object conforms to the specific rule in the given context.

        If the rule behaves different for each level/version, the level and version of the context will be used.

        Parameters:
        context - the validation context
        object - the object to validate
        Returns:
        false if the object does not respect the constraint

      • add

        public void add(AnyConstraint<T> c)
        Adds a constraint to the group.

        The constraints are collected in a Set, so every constraint can only be added once.

        Parameters:
        c - the constraint to add

      • remove

        public boolean remove(AnyConstraint<T> constraint)
        Removes the constraint from the group.
        Parameters:
        constraint - the constraint to remove
        Returns:
        true if constraint was in this group and was removed

      • contains

        public boolean contains(int errorCode)
        Checks if the errorCode is in the group.

        Notice that every ConstraintGroup uses the same error code CoreSpecialErrorCodes.ID_GROUP. Use contains(AnyConstraint) instead.

        Parameters:
        errorCode - the error code to search for
        Returns:
        true if the error code is in the group
        See Also:
        contains(AnyConstraint)
